title: Body found floating in Sydney Harbour near Darling Point

text:
A body has been found floating in Sydney Harbour just metres from the shore of exclusive eastern suburb Darling point.
A resident made the grisly discovery at 1.20pm on Friday and called emergency services, police say.
'Police from Rose Bay have set up a crime scene,' a spokeswoman said.
A body has been found in Sydney Harbour off Darling point, police investigating

The body was found near a park at the end of New Beach Road in the exclusive eastern suburb.
A well-used path runs along side the harbour near where the body was found.
The death does not appear to be suspicious, 7 News reports.
